# main.workflow.list
# Purpose: Entry point for project development
#
# Contract:
#   Pre:  Git repository is valid (git status works)
#   Post: Task completed, changes committed or discarded
#   Invariant: Repository remains valid throughout
#
# Unix Philosophy:
#   - Comments explain WHY, not WHAT
#   - If this gets complex, simplify (don't add comments)

# WHY: Need to know starting state before deciding what to do
- (status) Show current repository state
  - Run: git status --short
  - Run: git log --oneline -3

# WHY: Human intent drives the workflow, not the other way around
- (identify) Ask what task to perform
  - Ask: What do you want to do? (commit/push/release/other)

# WHY: Use existing automation if available, otherwise manual is fine
- (route) Execute based on choice
  - If commit:
    - Ask: Workflow exists? (yes/no)
    - If yes: Run workflow run commit
    - If no: Manual execution (git add, commit, etc.)
  - If push:
    - Run: git push
    - Optional: Check CI status
  - If other:
    - Manual execution

# WHY: Ensure repository is left in clean state
- (verify) Confirm final state
  - Run: git status
  - Ask: Repository in expected state? (yes/no)
  - If no: Fix before exiting

- End
